  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Health Response for Underserved Migrant Populations in Potential Drought Affected Areas in Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM will provide essential basic primary healthcare through a mobile health modality to ensure the extension of basic primary care inclusive of psychosocial support, child and maternal care, the provision of free medicines and emergency referrals to mobile populations. IOM will also seek to recruit vaccinators in close partnership with WHO and MoPH to ensure more equitable access to COVID-19 vaccinations, and social mobilizers to lead on associated Risk Communication and Community Engagement (RCCE) awareness raising campaigns for mobile populations, including returnees, internally displaced persons, nomads (kuchis) and underserved host communities. Overall health services through this project will benefit 225,000 persons.</narrative>
  </description>
